Files for Selenium and Zelenium
===============================

Selenium test files:

test_create_project.html
test_create_user.html
test_edit_project.html
test_login.html
test_logout.html

These may be run through the Selenium IDE.  A test suite file is
also available:  

TestSuite.html

There is also a python script, 'SeleniumTableRunner.py', that will run
these and other html table files via the python interface to Selenium RC.

The 'test_tal*' files are for Zelenium only and use TAL and the 
simple script 'configuration.py'.

In order to run the Zelenium tests using TAL and the value of 'baseURL' 
from the 'configuration.py' file:

1) Make a new 'Zuite' object in Zope
2) Add the following files as Page Templates, in order, to the Zuite:

test_tal_create_user.html
test_tal_login.html
test_tal_create_project.html
test_tal_edit_project.html
test_tal_logout.html

3) Add 'configuration.py' as a 'Script(Python)' object using the ID 'config'

4) Go to the url of te Zuite object and run the tests! [Note that you must run 
these not as the zope manager but as another user/profile.]